      "content": "The Supreme Court's interpretation of the 2nd Amendment has been a subject of debate, but the Court's current approach is more in line with the founders' intentions. The 2008 District of Columbia v. Heller decision, which established an individual right to bear arms, was a more accurate reading of the text, whereas the 2010 McDonald v. City of Chicago decision, which applied the 2nd Amendment to state and local governments, was a more judicial activism approach. The latter decision was criticized for overextending the scope of the 2nd Amendment, whereas the former decision was more narrowly tailored to the text.",
