      "content": "wait, i'm confused. if Heller was more \"accurate\" to the text, isn't saying McDonald was \"judicial activism\" kind of a biased way to look at it? i thought the whole point was that there are different valid ways to interpret the constitution, like living constitutionalism vs originalism. why do you think one is clearly more \"accurate\" than the other?",
