      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. you called originalism a \"flawed methodology\" though... isn't that just one school of thought? many legal scholars argue that originalism is actually the only way to prevent judges from just making up laws based on their own personal politics. why do you frame it as being objectively flawed versus just being a different legal philosophy?",
